(147, 5, 'Crawley', 'crawley', 'RH10', '01293 694001', '<p>Crawley is a large town and borough in West Sussex and covers an area of over 17 square miles with a population exceeding 100, 000. The area has been inhabited since the Stone Age  and has developed  from a market town since the 13th Century.</p>\r\n            <p>Crawley is the main feeder town for Gatwick Airport which is on the edge of the town to the North. The town is split into 13 neighbourhoods comprising   Langley Green, Northgate, Pound Hill, Maidenbower, Furnace Green, Tilgate, Broadfiled, Bewbush, Ifield, West Green, Gossops Green, Southgate, and Three Bridges. </p>\r\n            <p>Economically Crawley has developed in to the main industrial and employment centre between London to the north and Brighton on the south coast. </p>\r\n            <p>Crawley has a large shopping centre with an enclosed County Mall  precinct in the town centre.</p>'),
(148, 5, 'Crawley Down', 'crawley-down', 'RH10', '01342 445002', NULL),
(149, 5, 'East Grinstead', 'east-grinstead', 'RH19', '01342 445002', '<p>East Grinstead is a town and civil parish within the Mid Sussex district of West Sussex and  borders the village of Felbridge to the north west and is located in the Weald with Ashdown Forest sited to the south east of the town.</p>\r\n            <p>Towns close to East Grinstead include Tunbridge Wells to the east, Horley and Crawley to the west, and Redhill and Reigate to the north east. The population of East Grinstead stands at over 26,000.</p>\r\n            <p>The High Street boasts one of the longest continuous runs of 14th-century timber-framed buildings in England.</p>\r\n            <p>East Grinstead has a very diverse range of religious and spiritual organisations. There are places of worship for many christian denominations and also houses the UK headquarters for the Church of Scientology.</p>'),
