(153, 5, 'Horsham', 'horsham', 'RH12', '01403 856010', '<p>Horsham  is a market  town and in West Sussex.</p>\r\n            <p>Horsham is close to the outskirts of the Weald in West Sussex, on the upper stretches of the river Arun. The first historical record of Horsham is from AD 947. </p>\r\n            <p>Nearby Towns include Crawley sited to the north east and Haywards heath and Burgess Hill both sited to the south east.</p>\r\n            <p>Horsham has grown out from its original boundaries and now incorporates smaller hamlets that form part of the outer districts. These areas include Holbrook, Littlehaven, Needles, North Heath, Oakhill and Roffey.</p>\r\n            <p>Horsham  town centre comprises a carfax complex. Horsham is a commuter town that serves Gatwick airport, London and the south east. Historically Horsham was a  centre for horse trading, iron and brick making and more recently brewing.</p>'),
