(184, 3, 'Dorking', 'dorking', 'RH4', '01306 277005', '<p>Dorking is a market town in Surrey with a population of over 11,000 sited between  Leith Hill in the Greensand Ridge and Ranmore Common in the North Downs.</p>\r\n            <p>During the Georgian and Victorian periods six large sites within the former parish  boundaries of Dorking  were turned into grandiose  country estates: Leith Hill, Norbury Park, Denbies (which is now a vineyard and hotel) Polesdaen Lacey, Wolton House and Deepdene. Five of these estates now belong to the National Trust.</p>\r\n            <p>Dorking is a commuter and retirement settlement. It boasts three railway stations and is also home to the offices of multinational companies. </p>'),
