(200, 3, 'Redhill', 'redhill', 'RH1', '01737 471010', '<p>Redhill is a Surrey town in the borough of Reigate and Banstead. </p>\r\n            <p>To the west, Redhill adjoins the town of Reigate, and is also the commercial and entertainment area of the three adjoining communities of Earlswood, Merstham and Whitbushes, as well as the outlying rural villages of Bletchingley and Nutfield.</p>\r\n            <p>In commercial terms Redhill is a hub with offices of several large companies and a shopping centre within the town centre. However  a large proportion of the economically active population work in London, and is on the main train line between Brighton and London.</p>\r\n            <p>Redhill has an aerodrome sited approximately 1.7 miles south east that operates private commercial and pleasure flights as well as flying courses.</p>'),
(201, 3, 'Reigate', 'reigate', 'RH2', '01737 471010', '<p>Reigate is a town situated in East Surrey. It is within the London commuter belt and is one of the four towns within the borough of Reigate and Banstead, the other towns being Redhill, Horley, and Banstead.</p>\r\n            <p>Reigate is positioned at the foot of the North Downs and  has a population of over 20,000. In the winding lanes to the south-west of Reigate, in the direction of the Mole Valley, are the  hamlets, Skimmington and Flanchford. </p>\r\n            <p>Reigate has has been a market town since the medieval period and has a medieval castle.</p>\r\n            <p>The local economy is very diverse, with a strong local service sector as well as a large commuting population. In the 1980\'s Reigate was the first Surrey town for over a century to have a new brewery open within its boundaries.</p>\r\n            <p>Reigate has a long sprawling high street that serves as the main shopping area, where a lot of household names are present.</p>'),
